# bad_body
# ========
# One Perl regular expression per line, matched against a bounded article-body
# preview.  A hit is an unconditional rejection.  Use only unique, stable
# campaign markers that cannot plausibly occur in discussion, quotations,
# source code, spam reports, or FAQs.
#
# Exact campaign sentence, allowing variable whitespace:
# ^limited\s+time\s+offer\s+campaign-id-12345$
#
# Unique machine marker appearing anywhere in the scanned body:
# payload-id:\s*deadbeefcafebabe
#
# Exact contact phrase with flexible spacing:
# contact\s+abuse-campaign-2026@example\.invalid
#
# One of two unique tokens surrounded by non-word boundaries:
# (?:^|\W)(?:DROP-ID-4711|DROP-ID-8155)(?:\W|$)
#
# A fixed JSON-like key/value emitted by a specific bot.  Braces are escaped to
# make the intention obvious even though not every brace is special here:
# \{"campaign":"example-2026-07","id":[0-9]{8}\}
#
# Do NOT add "bitcoin", "casino", "viagra", generic URLs, =ybegin, MIME
# boundaries, Base64-looking text, or programming-language fragments.  Those
# cause severe false positives in technical and abuse-reporting groups.
